Chrome River and Meridian Global Services Launch Alliance to Streamline Travel and Expense Management and Compliance
[March 31, 2016]
Chrome River and Meridian Global Services Launch Alliance to Streamline Travel and Expense Management and Compliance
Tweet
Chrome
River, a leading provider of expense management and supplier invoice
processing software, today announced a new alliance relationship with
Meridian Global Services. The agreement further supports Chrome River's
strong growth trajectory across EMEA, as well as enabling it to deliver
a broader range of integrated solutions for its customers.
Meridian Global Services provides a range of international VAT and
travel and expense compliance and consulting services to over 15,000
clients worldwide. The alliance will enable customers of both
organisations to have an integrated solution for travel expense
submission and reporting, as well as VAT refund processing.
"Corporate travel managers want efficient, integrated solutions for
expense and VAT reimbursement, and with this alliance, we can make the
process much easier," said Nick Ludlow, general manager EMEA at Chrome
River. "Working with a trusted international brand such as Meridian
means that we can offer a richer solution for customers of both
companies, as well as open up Chrome River's trusted and robust solution
to a wider audience of business travelers."
"Chrome River and Meridian Global Services already share several
orporate customers across the UK, so extending our relationship was an
obvious solution," said Mark O'Riordan, CEO at Meridian Global Services.
"With this alliance, we look forward to strengthening our relationship,
and continuing our mission to streamline business travel for our
customers."
About Chrome River
Chrome River Technologies, Inc. provides expense reporting and supplier
invoice automation solutions that combine the latest enterprise and
mobile technologies with a team of industry-leading implementation and
support experts. Chrome River delivers immediate payback via a software
as a service delivery model that requires no hardware, no software, and
no long-term commitment. This service is easily configurable to meet the
needs of organisations worldwide with complex expense management
policies and collaborative approval processes. Request a demonstration
today and locate additional information about Chrome River and its
solutions by visiting the company website at www.chromeriver.com
or by calling +44 (0)20 7846 0166.
About Meridian Global Services
Meridian Global Services has provided international VAT services & tax
technology solutions to global businesses for over 27 years. We guide
our clients through the complexity of a global indirect tax compliance
environment and help them overcome indirect tax and complexity at both
the organisational and transactional level. Meridian are recognised
market leaders, with an expanding global presence in over 22 offices
worldwide and a reputation for delivering a quality of service
consistent with our mission of achieving client excellence. Over the
years we have enjoyed growing with our clients, listening and responding
to their needs, developing and tailoring ground-breaking services and
technology solutions in response to a constantly changing business and
legal environment.
To find out more about Meridian Global Services and the VAT Add-on,click
here.
View source version on businesswire.com: http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20160331005075/en/
